13:28.575 --> 13:32.410
♪ don't eat meat ♪

13:32.412 --> 13:34.479
♪ oh, no ♪

13:34.481 --> 13:37.916
♪ don't eat meat ♪

13:37.918 --> 13:39.284
- You don't have any drugs?
- Nope.

13:39.286 --> 13:40.451
- At all?
- None.

13:40.453 --> 13:41.986
- Secret stash of weed?
- Nada.

13:41.988 --> 13:43.254
Couple of vicodins maybe?

13:43.256 --> 13:44.756
I have a ton of inderal.

13:44.758 --> 13:46.457
I'll take some of that.
What does that do?

13:46.459 --> 13:47.592
- It's my heart medication.
- Oh, jesus christ.

13:47.594 --> 13:49.427
Helps with my arrhythmia.

13:49.429 --> 13:50.762
You don't have any
pain killers or anything?

13:50.764 --> 13:52.597
Listen to me,
you're just jonesing.

13:52.599 --> 13:54.933
- It will pass.
- [sighs]

13:54.935 --> 13:56.334
You don't take
anything anymore?

13:56.336 --> 13:58.269
- I take yoga.
- Oh, god.

13:58.271 --> 13:59.771
What, you can't picture
me doing yoga?

13:59.773 --> 14:01.272
Oh, no, no--i can picture
you doing yoga,

14:01.274 --> 14:02.607
But getting that picture
out of my head

14:02.609 --> 14:04.142
Is another reason i need
chemical assistance.

14:04.144 --> 14:05.510
Jesus, you in yoga pants?

14:05.512 --> 14:07.679
Man camel toe--bameltoe?
No, no thank you.

14:07.681 --> 14:09.480
That's a four-jameson job
right there.

14:09.482 --> 14:11.282
Have you ever heard
of "the art of now"?

14:11.284 --> 14:13.284
[sighs]
is it an art tatum record?

14:13.286 --> 14:14.619
No, it's a life movement.

14:14.621 --> 14:16.154
Breathe.
[inhales]

14:16.156 --> 14:16.988
Flow.
[exhales]

14:16.990 --> 14:18.489
Engage.

14:18.491 --> 14:19.624
So it's a sting record.

14:19.626 --> 14:21.626
You need to get open,
john.

14:21.628 --> 14:23.862
The answers to these questions
that you're asking yourself--

14:23.864 --> 14:26.631
They don't lie
at the bottom of a bottle

14:26.633 --> 14:28.333
Or the end of a rolled-up
dollar bill.

14:28.335 --> 14:29.534
You know where they lie?

14:29.536 --> 14:31.502
Right here.

14:31.504 --> 14:33.838
You got to cure
the addiction. I did.

14:33.840 --> 14:36.140
And so can you,
and i can help you, brother.

14:36.142 --> 14:37.976
The booze,
the blow, the weed--

14:37.978 --> 14:40.144
They were all
emotional crutches for me,

14:40.146 --> 14:43.348
Until i cast them aside
and learned to walk again,

14:43.350 --> 14:46.985
A free, clear,
fully grown man.

14:46.987 --> 14:48.319
[beeping]

14:48.321 --> 14:50.321
Yes!

14:50.323 --> 14:51.656
Bang, bang.

14:51.658 --> 14:53.658
Hot, hot, hot.
Hot--ow, ooh.

14:53.660 --> 14:55.159
Watch out, watch out.

14:55.161 --> 14:56.394
Are those tater tots?

14:56.396 --> 14:57.562
No.

14:57.564 --> 14:59.864
These are gluten-free
tater tots.

14:59.866 --> 15:00.865
Can you get me
the ketchup?

15:00.867 --> 15:03.334
Top shelf.
I can't reach.

15:03.336 --> 15:05.036
[sighs]

15:05.038 --> 15:06.404
Hot, hot.

15:10.577 --> 15:12.010
Hey, re,
how you doing?

15:12.012 --> 15:13.845
What?

15:13.847 --> 15:14.579
Nothing, just checking
on how you're doing

15:14.581 --> 15:15.680
And what's going on.

15:15.682 --> 15:17.582
- I'm fine.
- Cool.

15:17.584 --> 15:20.184
New axe? 'cause it's--
whew, it's killer.

15:20.186 --> 15:21.920
Same one i played
in the heathens.

15:21.922 --> 15:23.521
Oh, i--
it's just that it's so--

15:23.523 --> 15:24.923
You keep it so,
you know, shiny,

15:24.925 --> 15:28.092
It just looks like...

15:28.094 --> 15:29.961
Brand-new.

15:32.198 --> 15:34.265
I just--
i don't understand.

15:34.267 --> 15:36.434
There's always this weird,
you know, like, vibe between us.

15:36.436 --> 15:38.369
I don't--
i don't know why.

15:38.371 --> 15:40.538
Which one, like, the anger vibe
or the animosity vibe?

15:40.540 --> 15:42.907
Here's my current one:
I don't have any drugs.

15:42.909 --> 15:44.375
Who said anything
about drugs, dude? I

15:44.377 --> 15:46.377
Can't just walk in here
and tell my favorite bass player

15:46.379 --> 15:47.545
Of all time,
which is what--

15:47.547 --> 15:49.380
Bam texted me
30 seconds ago.

15:49.382 --> 15:51.416
I know you have pills
in one of these bags here, man,

15:51.418 --> 15:53.551
So don't tell me
that you don't, huh?

15:53.553 --> 15:56.754
They're prescription pills
prescribed by my doctor

15:56.756 --> 15:58.056
- For very specific reasons.
- Yeah.

15:58.058 --> 15:59.891
Come on, johnny!
Listen to me.

15:59.893 --> 16:02.727
Oh, jesus, what's your
doctor's name, duane reade?

16:02.729 --> 16:04.228
This is what keeps me
clean and sober.

16:04.230 --> 16:06.230
I'll bet. What the hell
are they all for, dude?

16:06.232 --> 16:08.633
Well, these kill panic.
These kill anxiety.

16:08.635 --> 16:10.234
These keep me
from killing myself.

16:10.236 --> 16:12.103
These keep me
from killing you.

16:12.105 --> 16:14.238
These keep the voices
at bay.

16:14.240 --> 16:15.473
You hear voices?

16:15.475 --> 16:16.975
I do.
I hear voices.

16:16.977 --> 16:18.576
Do you want to know
what they're saying?

16:18.578 --> 16:20.445
"give johnny
some percocets"?

16:20.447 --> 16:22.146
[chuckles]
these voices are

16:22.148 --> 16:25.783
From a very old age, my friend,
and they wish to sing,

16:25.785 --> 16:29.253
So i wrote them
a song cycle.

16:29.255 --> 16:31.823
What do you mean, like, a--
like a rock opera?

16:31.825 --> 16:33.925
Rock operas ain't hip
no more, bro.

16:33.927 --> 16:35.760
Song cycles--
uber hip.

16:35.762 --> 16:37.295
Yeah, right. I forgot
we live in brooklyn.

16:37.297 --> 16:38.463
Dig this.

16:38.465 --> 16:39.931
It's about the famine.

16:39.933 --> 16:41.165
The famine?

16:41.167 --> 16:43.935
Ireland, 1845.

16:43.937 --> 16:45.603
The awful blight
upon the potato crop?

16:45.605 --> 16:47.472
It's called<i> an gorta mor.</i>

16:47.474 --> 16:50.842
Oh. Is that, like, the name
of the main guy, like<i> tommy?</i>

16:50.844 --> 16:54.345
<i>An gorta mor</i> is gaelic
for "the great hunger."

16:54.347 --> 16:55.113
You want to hear it?

16:55.115 --> 16:56.981
Now?

16:56.983 --> 16:58.483
No, you don't
want to hear it.

16:58.485 --> 16:59.984
No, no, i do.

16:59.986 --> 17:01.285
No, this is what
i'm talking about.

17:01.287 --> 17:04.288
You are dismissive
of me.

17:04.290 --> 17:06.124
Back in the day,
you and flash

17:06.126 --> 17:08.126
Never let me contribute songs
to the heathens.

17:08.128 --> 17:09.627
- I know--
- not once.

17:09.629 --> 17:11.162
- That was a big mistake.
- You diminished me.

17:11.164 --> 17:12.463
You treated me like
a second-class citizen.

17:12.465 --> 17:14.198
Entwistle had songs
with the who!

17:14.200 --> 17:15.967
Paul mccartney
was the bass player!

17:15.969 --> 17:18.803
Paul simonon sang lead
on<i> guns of brixton!</i>

17:18.805 --> 17:22.173
God knows why, but rehab wants
to sing a song, forget it!

17:22.175 --> 17:24.342
- Verboten. God forbid.
- No, no, no, no.

17:24.344 --> 17:26.144
Listen, i want you
to contribute.

17:26.146 --> 17:27.712
That's one of the things
i wanted to talk to you about.

17:27.714 --> 17:29.213
I want you involved,
you know, i totally--

17:29.215 --> 17:31.349
I want to hear the--
what's it called, the song--

17:31.351 --> 17:33.484
- Cycle.
- Cycle, yes, yes.

17:33.486 --> 17:36.054
Cool.
Want to hear all 29 songs?

17:36.056 --> 17:38.556
You've wrote 29 songs
about the potato famine?

17:38.558 --> 17:40.058
Three million
people died.

17:40.060 --> 17:41.526
On an island
surrounded by fish.

17:41.528 --> 17:42.493
It lasted eight years.

17:42.495 --> 17:44.162
You got to really hate fish

17:44.164 --> 17:45.496
To not eat 'em
for eight years, re, i mean--

17:45.498 --> 17:47.031
They couldn't afford
to build boats,

17:47.033 --> 17:49.067
And the entire third hour
of the cycle is about that--

17:49.069 --> 17:52.170
Third hour? Is the cycle
longer than the actual famine?

17:52.172 --> 17:53.538
You just hear the first number,
and you tell me

17:53.540 --> 17:54.505
Whether or not it's right
for gigi.

17:54.507 --> 17:56.174
[sighs]
what's it called?

17:56.176 --> 17:57.408
<i>Bloody english horse.</i>

17:58.845 --> 17:59.544
You might have
to give me something

17:59.546 --> 18:01.412
To help me,
you know, focus.

18:01.414 --> 18:02.180
How about an adderall?

18:02.182 --> 18:04.215
What does it do?

18:04.217 --> 18:05.516
It's got a cocaine-type high,
lasts for five hours.

18:05.518 --> 18:07.051
Yes, perfect.

18:07.053 --> 18:08.419
One adderall,
coming up.

18:08.421 --> 18:10.354
Nice.

18:10.356 --> 18:14.559
♪ decaying while
we're left to die ♪

18:14.561 --> 18:18.896
♪ clouds of death
are in the sky ♪

18:18.898 --> 18:22.533
♪ this blight
on our potatoes ♪

18:22.535 --> 18:23.868
It's good.
I think i'm gonna

18:23.870 --> 18:25.603
Probably need
another one of these

18:25.605 --> 18:27.705
Just to get--you know,
really focus in on it.

18:27.707 --> 18:29.440
You're irish, man.
These are your people.

18:29.442 --> 18:30.875
- You should know about this.
- Well, you're jewish.

18:30.877 --> 18:32.610
Shouldn't you be writing
about the holocaust?

18:32.612 --> 18:35.213
The holocaust. It's got
such a history channel vibe now.

18:35.215 --> 18:36.881
Yeah.
Right.

18:36.883 --> 18:39.283
♪ and death and death
and death ♪

18:39.285 --> 18:40.418
Hi.

18:40.420 --> 18:41.853
[glass breaks]

18:46.926 --> 18:49.026
[sighs]

18:53.266 --> 18:54.565
This isn't gonna work.

18:54.567 --> 18:56.067
I know, right,
so we'll just

18:56.069 --> 18:57.568
Get rid of the blow,
and i'll just do

18:57.570 --> 19:00.071
The booze and the weed.

19:00.073 --> 19:02.073
You're right--no weed.
Just the booze.

19:02.075 --> 19:04.408
You have to get clean,
dad.

19:04.410 --> 19:06.077
I'm dead serious.

19:06.079 --> 19:07.411
I can tell, you haven't
looked at your phone

19:07.413 --> 19:08.746
In, like, four seconds.

19:08.748 --> 19:10.915
Do you care about me or not?
You can tell me.

19:10.917 --> 19:12.116
If you don't care about me,
you can tell me.

19:12.118 --> 19:13.584
Honey, of course
i care about you.

19:13.586 --> 19:15.253
Why would i get the band
back together again

19:15.255 --> 19:16.487
- If i didn't care about you?
You care about me

19:16.489 --> 19:17.922
Because, you know,
you think that i might be,

19:17.924 --> 19:19.290
Like, your last way
back into show business

19:19.292 --> 19:22.260
Or because i'm might make you
a ticket or two.

19:22.262 --> 19:24.328
A ticket is a million cash.

19:24.330 --> 19:26.264
I know what a ticket is.
I'm hip.

19:26.266 --> 19:27.765
I use--i say tickets.

19:27.767 --> 19:29.100
- Know what's funny?
- All the time.

19:29.102 --> 19:30.768
I've actually never
heard you say ticket.

19:30.770 --> 19:32.270
Well, you've only known me
for, like, a couple--

19:32.272 --> 19:34.172
Whose fault is that?

19:34.174 --> 19:36.340
Listen, i moved here
to find you, okay?

19:36.342 --> 19:37.508
I moved all of us in
together

19:37.510 --> 19:38.943
Because i don't want
to be alone.

19:38.945 --> 19:40.444
It's scary for me.

19:40.446 --> 19:42.280
Well, honey--it's pretty
scary for me too.

19:42.282 --> 19:44.148
I didn't know that
this was gonna happen.

19:44.150 --> 19:46.117
I'm just trying to get
used to it, you know?

19:46.119 --> 19:48.786
Honey, i'm not just
doing this, you know,

19:48.788 --> 19:50.955
Like, some addict.
I'm an artist.

19:50.957 --> 19:52.790
The reason that i drink
and i do drugs

19:52.792 --> 19:54.525
Is because it unleashes
my subconscious

19:54.527 --> 19:55.693
When i'm writing songs.

19:55.695 --> 19:57.028
And the rock and roll
hall of fame

19:57.030 --> 19:58.629
Is full of people
who do that, okay?

19:58.631 --> 20:00.031
I mean, i don't want
you doing it.

20:00.033 --> 20:01.132
You don't drink
or do drugs, right?

20:01.134 --> 20:03.034
- No.
- Good. Glad to hear it.

20:03.036 --> 20:05.136
Why not?

20:05.138 --> 20:07.138
Because i'm a singer, dad.
My voice is my instrument.

20:07.140 --> 20:09.173
Right, and i'm a songwriter,
and i need it.

20:09.175 --> 20:10.641
I don't want you doing it

20:10.643 --> 20:12.043
'cause it would
destroy your voice,

20:12.045 --> 20:13.811
But for me,
it's necessary.

20:13.813 --> 20:15.313
Yeah, well, it might destroy
the few brain cells

20:15.315 --> 20:17.215
You have left.

20:17.217 --> 20:19.650
And your relationship
with your only daughter.

20:19.652 --> 20:21.385
This is a wake-up call, dad.

20:21.387 --> 20:24.188
You missed the first
20 years of my life.

20:24.190 --> 20:27.358
I think that it would be nice if
you were around for the next 20.

20:27.360 --> 20:29.894
Okay.

20:29.896 --> 20:32.029
[sighs]
i get it.

20:32.031 --> 20:34.031
Can i ask you one thing?

20:34.033 --> 20:35.166
Don't date flash.

20:35.168 --> 20:36.901
Yeah--no, you have
no say in that.

20:36.903 --> 20:38.002
I'm--
[sighs]

20:38.004 --> 20:39.337
Hey, i date
who i want to date.

20:39.339 --> 20:40.838
Maybe if i had
a father who cared

20:40.840 --> 20:42.673
I wouldn't be so hung up
on father figures.

20:42.675 --> 20:44.041
- Give me the pills.
- What pills?

20:44.043 --> 20:46.644
The pills in your hand.
Give me the [bleep] pills.

20:48.548 --> 20:51.749
Okay, there are two.
Thank you.

20:55.221 --> 20:56.520
[buzzing]

20:56.522 --> 20:57.922
[slurping]

20:57.924 --> 20:59.290
[sighs]

21:02.395 --> 21:05.196
[guitar strumming]

21:05.198 --> 21:13.304
♪ ♪

21:16.276 --> 21:19.043
[humming]

21:19.045 --> 21:25.716
♪ ♪

21:25.718 --> 21:28.386
All right, guys, so it's
not done, by any means.

21:28.388 --> 21:30.554
It's just a verse and
a beginning of a chorus, so--

21:30.556 --> 21:32.657
[clears throat]
here goes.

21:34.227 --> 21:35.092
[exhales]

21:35.094 --> 21:38.095
[guitar strumming]

21:38.097 --> 21:45.403
♪ ♪

21:45.405 --> 21:50.574
♪ i stand alone
in the city of lights ♪

21:50.576 --> 21:53.311
♪ i stand alone tonight ♪

21:53.313 --> 21:56.080
♪ ♪

21:56.082 --> 22:00.918
♪ i hear the moaning
of the misbegotten souls ♪

22:00.920 --> 22:03.988
♪ mining sinner's gold ♪

22:03.990 --> 22:06.090
♪ ♪

22:06.092 --> 22:10.094
♪ mining sinner's gold ♪

22:10.096 --> 22:11.429
♪ ♪

22:11.431 --> 22:13.998
♪ mining sinner's gold ♪

22:14.000 --> 22:16.434
♪ ♪

22:16.436 --> 22:19.303
♪ mining sinner's gold ♪

22:19.305 --> 22:21.605
♪ ♪

22:21.607 --> 22:25.476
♪ mining sinner's gold ♪

22:25.478 --> 22:26.677
[song ends]

22:28.448 --> 22:30.047
What'd you think?

22:34.354 --> 22:35.286
I'll go get some whiskey.

22:35.288 --> 22:36.454
Who's got weed?

22:36.456 --> 22:38.289
My pill bag is in the van.

22:38.291 --> 22:39.657
(flash)
i've got a one-hitter.
Colorado shit.

22:39.659 --> 22:41.192
(ira)
better get some vodka too.

22:41.194 --> 22:42.693
You know what,
if he's gonna get high,

22:42.695 --> 22:45.329
He's gonna get hungry--
i'll get some pizza.

22:45.331 --> 22:48.299
But i thought my health was
the most important thing.

22:48.301 --> 22:51.535
Dad, that song sounded like
something that sting would write

22:51.537 --> 22:54.138
If he was living inside
sarah mclachlan's vagina.

22:54.140 --> 22:56.140
You need to get high.
But no more blow--that's over.

22:56.142 --> 22:57.375
Baby, i got some darvon

22:57.377 --> 22:58.509
In the medicine cabinet.
Help yourself.

22:58.511 --> 23:00.311
Okay, uh--

23:00.313 --> 23:02.446
Sorry, guys.
I-i did my best.

23:05.184 --> 23:06.984
Yes!

23:06.986 --> 23:10.388
Hello, darvon.

23:10.390 --> 23:14.358
(rehab)
♪ i saw the living, dying,
and the nearly dead ♪

23:14.360 --> 23:18.028
♪ ♪

23:18.030 --> 23:21.565
♪ people fighting
for a tiny crust of bread ♪

23:21.567 --> 23:25.836
♪ ♪

23:25.838 --> 23:28.906
♪ potatoes once
of brown and gold ♪

23:40.353 --> 23:42.253
Why'd the band break up?

23:42.255 --> 23:44.088
His ego.
Your ego.

23:44.090 --> 23:46.524
His ego.
Your ego, and you slept
with my wife.

23:46.526 --> 23:48.526
Your wife slept with me.
See, he flips it.

23:48.528 --> 23:52.196
No. If i admit that i slept
with your wife, after 25 years,
will you finally forgive me?

23:52.198 --> 23:54.365
